import pandas as pd
import plotly.express as px
import plotly.graph_objects as go
import sqlite3 as sq3
import numpy as np

con = sq3.connect("opioid.db")
sql = con.cursor()


for row in sql.execute("select * from annual where countyfips = 'NA' and BUYER_STATE != 'PR' limit 10;"):
    print(row)

pop_info = pd.read_sql_query("SELECT * from population", con)
ann_info = pd.read_sql_query("SELECT * from annual", con)
land_info = pd.read_sql_query("SELECT * from land", con)

con.close

# print(ann_info.loc[(ann_info.countyfips=='NA') & (ann_info.BUYER_STATE != 'PR')][0:20])
# print(ann_info.iloc[range(17429,17438), 6])
ann_info.iloc[range(17429,17438), 6]= 5097
print(ann_info.loc[(ann_info.BUYER_COUNTY=='MONTGOMERY') & (ann_info.BUYER_STATE == 'AR')])
ann_na=ann_info.loc[ann_info['BUYER_COUNTY'] != 'NA']

land_area= land_info[ ['Areaname', 'STCOU', 'LND110210D']]
land_area=land_area.rename(columns={'STCOU':'countyfips'})
land_area.head()

# population left join land_area
print(pop_info.head())
county_info = pd.merge(land_area, pop_info, on = 'countyfips')
print(county_info.head())

print("# of records from land = ", land_info.shape[0])
print("# of records from land_area = ", land_area.shape[0])
print("# of records from county_info = ", county_info.shape[0])
print("# of records from population = ", pop_info.shape[0])

## ann_info ##27758 rows
## ann_na  ##27741 rows, delete missing BUYER_COUNTY

ann_naST = ann_na.drop(['BUYER_COUNTY', 'countyfips', 'count'], axis = 1)
print(ann_naST.head(3))

ann_naST = ann_naST.assign( Dose = ann_naST.DOSAGE_UNIT.astype(float))
ann_naST = ann_naST.assign( Year = ann_naST.year.astype(int))
print(ann_naST.head(3))

ann_STmean = ann_naST.groupby(['Year']).Dose.mean().reset_index().rename(columns = {'Dose' : 'Avg_Dose_States'})
ann_STmean


ann_naST = ann_na.drop(['countyfips'], axis = 1)
ann_naST.head(5)

ann_naST = ann_naST.assign( CountyDose = ann_naST.DOSAGE_UNIT.astype(float))
ann_naST = ann_naST.assign( Year = ann_naST.year.astype(int))
ann_naST = ann_naST.drop(['DOSAGE_UNIT', 'year'], axis = 1)
print(ann_naST.head(5))

ann_subset = ann_naST.groupby(['Year', 'BUYER_STATE']).sum().reset_index().rename(columns = {'CountyDose' : 'State_Annual_Dose'})
ann_subset.head(10)
ann_naST = ann_naST.assign( State_Annual_Dose = ann_subset.State_Annual_Dose)
ann_naST.head()


fig = px.scatter(ann_naST
           ,x = 'Year'
           ,y = 'State_Annual_Dose'
           ,color = 'BUYER_STATE'
           ,size='CountyDose'
           ,hover_data=['BUYER_STATE']   
           )

fig.show()
